@node "tech" "Tech Notes"

    TECH NOTES

    There are a few things you _should_ know before using this library.

    This wonder has been written using AmigaE V3.2a by Wouter van Oortnerssen.
    In the docs Wouter warns this:

    (from E.Guide)

       libraries created by E should be opened/closed by
   any one task EXACTLY ONCE, not more, not less (this shouldn't pose any
   problems though).  If you put your library in the PD, you will want to put a
   programmers notice in your docs mentioning this.  Strange things WILL happen
   if you don't obey this rule.



    By the way, AmigaE is a very powerful, object oriented, typeless language.
    It is easy to learn and you will create masterpieces in a few months...
    Why do not give it a look? The full package (with a demo version of the
    compiler) is on Aminet under dev/e directory.
    Registration fee is about $40 if I do not get wrong.

    In my opinion: the best language for the Amiga fanatic!

@endnode

@node "error_table" "ERROR TABLE"

ERROR NUMBER        DESCRIPTION
----------------------------------------------------------------
 0                  No Error
-1                  Alloc Error
-2                  Open Error (usually it is a File Not Found)
-3                  OpenIFF Error
-4                  DoChunk Error  (Could not CollectionChunk() correctly)
-5                  Set Stop Error (could not StopOnExit() correctly)
@endnode
